      "amount": "1/4 cup",
      "notes": "chopped"
    }
  ],
  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood-fired oven to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together coconut cream, olive oil, garlic, ginger, cumin, coriander, paprika, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Add the chicken breast to the bowl and coat with the marinade.",
    "Place the chicken in a molcajete and pour the remaining marinade over the top.",
    "Bake the chicken in the preheated oven for 35 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the oven and sprinkle with chopped parsley.",
    "Return the chicken to the oven and bake for an additional 10 minutes.",
    "Remove the chicken from the oven and let rest for 5 minutes before serving."
